settings.value: Our tool uses advanced algorithms to analyze the complexity of your code. settings.value:
1. Analyze Code: Our tool scans your Python code and uses the algorithm to measure its complexity.
  2. Assign Scores: Each part of your code is assigned a complexity score.

settings.name: content
settings.value:
Simplifying your code has several benefits for sustainable coding practices:

  • Efficiency: Simpler code is more efficient. It requires less computing power to run, which reduces energy usage and carbon emissions.
  • Maintainability: Simpler code is easier to maintain. This reduces the time and resources required for code maintenance, further reducing its environmental impact.
  • Longevity: Simpler code is more likely to be reusable and adaptable to future changes, increasing its lifespan and reducing the need for new code to be written.
